<title>USA: Larcan-TTC to be bought for $0.625/shr.</title>
<headline>Larcan-TTC to be bought for $0.625/shr.</headline>
<dateline>LOUISVILLE, Colo. 1997-07-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Larcan-TTC Inc said Friday it agreed to be acquired by majority shareholder Larcan Inc for $0.625 a share.</p>
<p>The producer of television and radio equipment said Larcan, a majority-owned subsidiary of Canada's private LeBlanc &amp; Royle Enterprises Inc, already owns 78.4 percent of the company.</p>
<p>Under the merger agreement, each Larcan-TTC share will be cancelled in for $0.0625 in cash, the company said.</p>
<p>The company's stock closed at 1/16 (or $0.625) Thursday.</p>
